// Test specific file
" npx playwirght test FileName "
//------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->
//Test specific file using browser
" npx playwright test FileName --project='Google Chrome' "
//------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->
// CodeGen tool
" npx playwright codegen "
//------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->
// Playwright hooks
1. beforeAll() -> code block will be executed before running all tests
2. beforeEach() -> code block will be executed before running each and every tests
3. afterAll() -> code block will be executed after running each and every tests
4. afterEach() -> code block will be executed after running all tests
//------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->
// If we expect some text in playwright we will use "expect", Example Below:
" await expect(page.locator("#dropdown-class-example > option")).toHaveText(['option1', 'option2', 'option3']) "
//------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->
// Multiple elements, we need to switch into iframe first then perform tasks, Example Below:
    const iframe = page.frameLocator('[class="demo-frame"]');
    const dragElement = iframe.locator("div[id='draggable'] p");
//------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->
// Assertions in Playwright
    " There are 2 types of Asserstions: Hard and Soft "
    1. Hard Assertions - if test fails it will stop the text execution
    2. Soft Assertions - if test fails it will continue the test till the end of the test case.

    a) Editable - toBeEditable()
    b) Visible - toB Visible ()
    c) Enabled - toBeEnabled ()
    d) Empty - toBeEmpty ()

    e) URL - toHaveURL ()
    f) Title - to Have Title ()
    g) Text - toHave Text ()
    h) Count - toHaveCount ()
    i) Disabled - toBeDisabled ()
//------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->
